<title>USA: Standard Pacific to sell $100 mln in debt.</title>
<headline>Standard Pacific to sell $100 mln in debt.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard Pacific Corp on Tuesday said it will sell $100 million in senior notes from its outstanding shelf registration.</p>
<p>Proceeds from the offering will be used to pay down indebtedness under the company's revolving credit agreement.</p>
<p>The company did not provide a time frame for the offering.</p>
<p>Standard Pacific operates primarily as a geographically diversified builder of single family homes with operations throughout major metropolitan markets in California and Texas.</p>
<p>((--U.S. Corporate Bond Unit, 212-859-1672))</p>
